President Joe Biden and President Pedro Sánchez of Spain discussed preparations for the NATO Summit during their conversation. The summit will take place in Madrid on June 29-30, 2022. Both leaders expressed excitement about the upcoming trip and appreciated the opportunity to meet in person. President Biden thanked President Sánchez for hosting the summit, which will focus on NATO's transformation in the next ten years. President Biden also commended Spain for its cooperation in responding to Russia's war in Ukraine, including providing security and humanitarian aid to Ukraine and supporting sanctions against Russia.